Swiss aviation startup Sirius Aviation unveiled the world’s first hydrogen-powered Vertical Take-Off and Landing (#VTOL) aircraft, the Sirius Jet. Developed in collaboration with BMW’s Designworks and Sauber Group, the hydrogen-electric VTOL aircraft merges jet aerodynamics with #helicopter versatility. The #Sirius Business Jet, offering a 1,150-mile flight range, and the #SiriusMillenniumJet, designed for commercial #aviation with a 650-mile range, are set to launch in 2025. The project involves key partnerships with #BMW Group’s DesignWorks, Sauber Group, Alfleth Engineering AG, and ALD Group, aiming to pioneer sustainable and high-performance aviation solutions.
